For smaller interest in politics $q<0.641$ the distribution would lead to a U-shape with a higher amount of never attached and a lower amount of always attached individuals. For higher interest in politics $q<0.641$ the bin with always attached individuals would be even higher and the bin with never attached individuals even lower. In the paper, we analysed if this would realize when we subdivide our sample based on the survey question about individuals' political interest in the \textcite{GSPS2010datayears1984-2010}. It turns out that fitting the model parameter $q$ for the different subsamples of people gives us $q=0.82$ for individuals with very strong political interest, $q=0.7$ for strong, $q=0.58$ for weak, and $q=41$ for no interest in politics. 

